               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc>
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <p>Fragments of two or more uniform <objectType>panel</objectType>s of grey <material>marble</material> ( <dimensions> 
                                 <width unit="metre">not calculable</width> 
                                 <height unit="metre">0.405</height>
                                 <depth unit="metre">0.041</depth>
                              </dimensions>).
               The surviving dimensions correspond exactly to those of the recess which contained the dedicatory inscription of the quadruple tetrapylon 
               base in the Portico behind the Theatre, a monument of the characteristic Severan materials and workmanship, which may be conjectured 
               to have been dedicated to Septimius Severus, Julia Domna, Caracalla and Geta.  
               Some of the surviving fragments, here attributed to Septimius Severus and Caracalla, could equally well refer to any of the four members of the Severan dynasty.</p>
